{
	"name": "Cutting Words",
	"type": "feat",
	"system": {
		"description": {
			"value": "<p><em>You demoralize an enemy at a critical moment, pushing them to fail rather than succeed.</em></p><p><strong>Reaction</strong> - 1 Creature (60 ft.) - Magical</p><p><em>Trigger: An enemy hits with an attack roll or succeeds a skill check (you cannot use this ability on saving throws). The enemy must be able to hear you.</em></p><p>You expend a use of @UUID[Compendium.elkan5e.elkan5e-class-features.Item.kg7VBahhFH6gDFIh]{Bardic Inspiration} to use this ability.</p><ul><li><p>You roll your bardic inspiration die and subtract the number from the total, potentially turning the success into a failure. </p></li><li><p>If you have the @UUID[Compendium.elkan5e.elkan5e-class-features.Item.QIiLoZgVJqdEguAX]{Counterpoint} feature, you don't expend a use of Bardic Inspiration when the target succeeds their roll.</p></li></ul>",
